# Site-Kit Publishing

When publishing `@uptrademedia/site-kit` to npm:

1. Build first: `cd packages/site-kit && pnpm build`
2. Publish with: `pnpm publish --no-git-checks --access public`
3. **Do NOT pass `--otp`** — the user will handle authentication interactively when prompted.
4. After publishing, update consuming projects (e.g. coachlight-nextjs) with `pnpm install` or update the version in package.json.

## Local linking does NOT work

Do **not** attempt to use `pnpm link`, `link:`, or `file:` protocols to test site-kit locally in Next.js projects. Next.js 16 Turbopack cannot resolve subpath exports from linked packages outside the project root. Always publish to npm and install the published version.
